title: Grateful Dead Live at Silva Hall, Hult Center on 1984-05-08
description:
Set 1

Beer Barrel Polka, Jack Straw, Cold Rain & Snow, Minglewood Blues, Candyman, Me & My Uncle, Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Looks Like Rain-> Might As Well

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Touch Of Gray-> Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums*-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> I Need A Miracle-> Morning Dew, E: Sugar Magnolia, E: Brokedown Palace

*with Ken Kesey and the Thunder Machine

reviews.review_text:
Intense! One of my "go to" Other Ones, super intense and sustained middle jam, Jerry doesn't want to stop!

OK, so on this day, exactly 7 years on from Cornell maybe they aren't the same band, but whatever... just enjoy.

Brokedown Palace for Kesey family Ken Kesey and family were present at this show, that took place some months after Ken Kesey lost his son in a car accident. The Dead closed this show with Brokedown palace, and as the song  develops all the band starts turning to face Kesey family. Then the audience turned and faced them. By the time they got to "fare thee well" everyone was crying and there was no applause at the end, the whole arena knowing and understanding. You can hear Kesey talking about this episode in a conference at University of Virginia here (00:26:20):
https://youtu.be/pacbkF1KWCI
